  "text": "We looked at the results for the time course of the loss of the ring-X as revealed by progeny counts at different times of male aging. No simple relationship was found. The relationship over time is expected to be a complex one. An increase in recombination events is expected owing to the accumulation of events in aging stem cells [CITATION_1] . This is, however, expected to be balanced by a loss of P elements due to simple excision. The failure to detect a simple relationship may therefore be due to the canceling out of these two forces.",
